  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the sliced onion and cook until softened, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the basmati rice and cook for 1-2 minutes, until lightly toasted.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes, until the rice is cooked and the liquid has been absorbed.",
    "Stir in the grated cheddar cheese and crushed black pepper.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
